#: ../../../spi/multiple-data-lanes.rst:5
msgid ""
"Some specialized SPI controllers and peripherals support multiple data lanes "
"that allow reading more than one word at a time in parallel. This is "
"different from dual/quad/octal SPI where multiple bits of a single word are "
"transferred simultaneously."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../spi/multiple-data-lanes.rst:10
msgid ""
"For example, controllers that support parallel flash memories have this "
"feature as do some simultaneous-sampling ADCs where each channel has its own "
"data lane."
msgstr ""

